Mail Sending Error Fix

Problem Summary
- Signup OTP API (`POST /api/v1/auth/sendotp`) returned HTTP 500 in production on Render.
- Render logs showed: `Error sending mail: Connection timeout`.

What Was Happening In Code
- OTP generation calls `OTP.create(...)`.
- `OTP` model has a pre-save hook that sends email before save completes.
- Email sending originally used SMTP via Nodemailer on port 587.
- When SMTP call timed out, the hook threw an error, so OTP save failed, and API returned 500.

Root Cause
- Render free web services block outbound traffic on SMTP ports (25, 465, 587).
- Because SMTP connection could not be established, mail sending failed with timeout.

Why We Switched From SMTP To Brevo HTTP API
- SMTP requires blocked ports on this hosting tier.
- Brevo HTTP API uses HTTPS over port 443, which is allowed on Render free tier.
- Port 443 is reliable and generally available across hosting environments.

What Changed
- Replaced Nodemailer SMTP transport with Brevo HTTP request:
  - Endpoint: `https://api.brevo.com/v3/smtp/email`
  - Method: POST
  - Auth header: `api-key: BREVO_API_KEY`
- Sender info now comes from env vars:
  - `MAIL_FROM`
  - `MAIL_FROM_NAME`
  - `BREVO_API_KEY`

Result
- OTP and other email flows no longer depend on blocked SMTP ports.
- Mail sending works through HTTPS (443), so signup OTP can succeed on Render free tier.

Important Deployment Notes
- Keep secrets only in Render environment variables; do not commit `.env`.
- Ensure `MAIL_FROM` is a verified sender in Brevo.
- Free-email senders (e.g., Gmail) may work for testing but can have lower deliverability due to DKIM/DMARC compliance warnings.
